# Never convert line endings on checkout/checkin.
#
# WHY THIS MATTERS (auto-update integrity):
# make_update_manifest.py hashes the WORKING-TREE bytes of each ENGINE_FILE, and
# the launcher verifies those hashes against the files it fetches from
# raw.githubusercontent.com — which serves the COMMITTED (LF) blob bytes.  On the
# Windows CI runner, git's default core.autocrlf=true would check the .py/.html
# files out as CRLF, so the manifest would hash CRLF while the fleet fetches LF —
# every SHA-256 would mismatch and auto-update would silently, permanently fail.
# Forcing "-text" (treat every path as binary → no EOL conversion) guarantees the
# working tree is byte-identical to the committed blobs on every platform.
* -text
